HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 181
BY REPRESENTATIVE MELERINE
A RESOLUTION
To commend Louisiana State University at Shreveport for the success of its athletic
program.
WHEREAS, the Louisiana State University at Shreveport (LSUS) baseball team
completed its 2025 season by winning the NAIA World Series and completing the only
perfect season in college baseball history; and
WHEREAS, the team won its first seven games in 2026 and stretched its consecutive
game win streak to sixty-six straight games, which is the longest win streak in college
baseball history; and
WHEREAS, the LSUS men's and women's basketball teams each won Red River
Athletic Conference titles, and the men advanced to the Sweet 16 of the NAIA Men's
Basketball National Championship tournament; and
WHEREAS, the LSUS men's and women's soccer teams each won Red River
Athletic Conference titles; and
WHEREAS the LSUS men's soccer team advanced to the NAIA Men's Soccer
National Championship tournament; and
WHEREAS the LSUS weightlifting team finished its season ranked second
nationally; and
WHEREAS, Louisiana State University at Shreveport is most deserving of
recognition for the incredible achievements of its athletic program.
